bbcl - bitlbee contact list for irc it
======================================

This small program prints out contact list of users connecting to bitlbee[2]
client from output made by ii[1]. The contact list is updated with every new
line incoming to the standard input of bbcl.

It works only for bitlbee<->ii scenario.

It uses ANSI escape codes to format output.

Building
--------

To build bbcl simply type make. You may want change config.mk depending on your
system.

Running bbcl
------------

Simply put ii out file to the standard input of bbcl.

Example
-------

$ tail -fn0 ~/irc/localhost/out | bbcl

[1] http://tools.suckless.org/ii/
[2] https://www.bitlbee.org/
